'''Jedok geom''' or ''Admiral sword'' or ''Commander sword'' is the name of sword-skill introduced by the Chinese commander [[Li Rusong]] who fought during the [[Japanese invasions of Korea (1592<U+2013>1598)|Imjin waeran]] on Korea's side against the Japanese. Li Rusong was of Korean descent. 

==Technique==
The techniques required the use of both a sharp sword and a waist sword. Li used straight-bladed swords (jikdo) with a single edge for slashing and a double-edged sword (geom) for stabbing. The techniques, with 14 basic stances, were first published in the [[Muyesinbo]], a martial arts manual from the [[Joseon Dynasty]].
 
The skill required both a sharp sword and a waist sword in 14 basic techniques. Li used straight<U+2010>bladed swords (jikdo) taking advantage of the strength of a single<U+2010>edged sword (do) for slashing and a double<U+2010>edged sword (gom) for stabbing.

